==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Giggot
<hw>Gig"got</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr></mhw>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. OF. <ets>gigue</ets> fiddle; -- on account
of the resemblance in shape. See <er>Jig</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A leg of mutton.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A small piece of flesh; a slice.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The rest in <qex>giggots</qex> cut, they spit.</q>
<rj><qau>Chapman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gigue</ent>⟦br⟧
